The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | The City Diary
                                                                                                               The City Diary
                Jewellery, a TV set and other valuables worth more than Rs 1.5 lakh and Rs 80,000 in cash were stolen from a house in Parnasree, Behala. The residents, Sankhadip Dasgupta and his family, were in Guwahati and returned home on Monday. Police said the theft was discovered by the domestic help who turned up at the house before the family.    A 45-year-old man allegedly surrendered at Tangra police station on Monday after murdering his wife. Police said a drunk Prabir Halder was fighting with wife Brihaspati when he stabbed her with a knife on Sunday night. Prabirs daughter Ritu, who claimed to have witnessed the murder, told sleuths that her father had tried to lock her in a room after finding her awake but she managed to escape. Neighbours took Brihaspati to NRS hospital where she was declared dead.     A 22-year-old youth was arrested on Sunday evening for allegedly raping a 13-year-old on Saptami evening. Kartik Mondol was picked up from his Chitpur Lockgate house. Police said Mondol had fled to a relatives house in the Sunderbans and returned on Sunday.    A 75-year-old woman was found hanging at her Netaji Pally home in Kanchrapara on Monday morning. Police said Chapala Mondal, who had been suffering from cancer for the past four years, had committed suicide. The body has been sent for post-mortem.     An unidentified man in his 40s committed suicide by jumping in front of a local train between Belur and Liluah stations around 7am on Monday. The body has been sent for post-mortem.    A woman in her late 20s was arrested on Bright Street, in Park Circus, on Monday for allegedly trying to snatch the earrings of a seven-year-old girl. Ruksana Begum, a resident of the area, allegedly lured Firdaus with a chocolate and tried to take away her earrings. But the child could sniff Ruksanas plot and started screaming, alerting residents.     Around 200 shanty dwellers and members of a human rights organisation demonstrated outside the urban development office in Salt Lake for two hours on Monday demanding immediate rehabilitation of the people whose houses were razed on Sunday. The people also met the urban development secretary. The human rights organisation would submit a memorandum on the issue on Tuesday.    The body of 18-year-old Bikash Shaw, who drowned in the Hooghly near Cossipore on Sunday, was found near Jagannath Ghat on Monday. The factory workers body has been sent for post-mortem.    A high-level meeting on the proposed flyover on Raja SC Mullick Road was held at Writers Buildings on Monday. The meeting was presided over by chief secretary Ashok Mohan Chakrabarti.     The Armed Forces Recruitment Directorate has set up an interactive voice response system (IVRS) in Hindi, English and Bengali for West Bengal, Orissa and Sikkim to disseminate information on entry parameters. The IVRS number is 22235253.            
